contents: "The next morning, the first thing I heard upon entering the classroom was a loud sneeze that made me want to turn my heel. Kamogawa was sniffling miserably.

My good morning mood had completely gone down the drain. I hurried to my desk while persuading myself that I had heard nothing; that there was no person called Kamogawa.

On my way, I noticed that Youko Tsukimori's seat was still empty—which was rare for someone as well-bred as her.

The moment I sat down, "nyakchun," I heard a loose sneeze that resembled the dying cry of a cat that was pancaked by a road roller from besides.

"Ah, mnorning, Nyomnomiphya."",

contents: "That evening.

After working for a while at the café, moving my limp body, Konan suddenly came rushing in with am energized face that virtually screamed that he was in peak form. "I dished out 3,000 yen<ref>About 40$</ref> to get me some aphrodisiac, and I'm feeling great after sleeping over it<!-- He drunk it, then he slept. -->, baby!"

"I'm pleased to hear that," I uttered perfunctorily, causing Konan to raise an eyebrow.

"Oh, looks like you aren't feeling too well today, huh?" he asked, so I told him that I had been feeling limp since the morning.

"Nonomiya-kun, that's a cold!" he declared. Because that actually made sense to me, I nodded, muttering "I see..."

"I bet you picked it up from someone, right?"

"...Who knows? At least I don't."

Had I really contracted a cold from someone, it was quite likely to be the person I had spent a night with, but there was naturally no way I would ever honestly tell Konan that.

That said, it was quite apparent that I would hear that name from him whether I kept silent or not.

"Well, it must have been Youko-chan, right? You slept naked together, right?! Spit it, Nonomiya-kun!"

"Let me pose a counter question: to someone like you, who claims to be richly experienced, do we really look like that?" I asked calmly while keeping an eye on Tsukimori who was waiting a table on the other side of the café.

"Mmmm," Konan grumbled for a few moments, "...Haah... yeah, you still don't look like you have crossed the line."

I put a coffee cup on his table and turned around to the kitchen. But Konan shouted something at me from behind.

"—Ah right right, there's one more possible reason that I forgot to mention."

I ignored him and headed to the kitchen, convinced that it was not worth my time.


"Did you know that you can get infected if someone kisses you?"


I smiled wryly when it turned out that it had really not been worth my time. As I did not remember such an event, I just replied with a wave of my hand.

Suddenly, I noticed the smell of roses in my nose and turned around. Right behind me was a softly smiling Youko Tsukimori.

"You don't look well; have you caught a cold? It's my turn now to nurse you in return for yesterday. There's no need for restraint, so feel free to depend on me as much as you like!"

"I'm good, thanks. I don't want to be in your debt."

"Now, now, Nonomiya-kun, you can be so stubborn about certain things!"

I ignored her sulky words and started to sort the bills. But I stopped right away.

Before my eyes, I saw Youko Tsukimori taking a lip balm out of her apron and applying it to her lips.

Apparently she noticed my gaze.

"The air is dry during this time of the year, so my lips get rough if I don't regularly give them moisture, you see," she explained as she moved her lips to distribute the moisture.<!-- Not really appropriate, but I have no idea how to write it. She applied it, and now she's kinda pushing her lips out and... in to, you know, "make her lips become familiar with the balm" It's quite usual to do that, but no idea how it's described. -EEE --> My eyes were following her lustrous lips' every movement.

"...Tsukimori."

"Mm? Do you want to use it, too?"

"Ah, no, I don't need it..."

I averted my eyes almost as if to escape from her.

"You're acting strange, Nonomiya-kun. Maybe you should call it a day?" she giggled.

"I think I'll do just that...," I answered while shaking my head.

I didn't trust myself to do any proper work today anymore. I had a horrible temperature. I felt hot not only in my face, but up to my ears.<!-- But not because of illness... -EEE -->

There was a question that itched on my tongue, but I was absolutely not in the condition to ask. But there were a few facts that were clear to me even without asking.

Firstly, that she was in the best of health.

Secondly, that she had been in high spirits ever since this morning.

Lastly—

This happened when I passed Tsukimori by on my way to the staffroom. In a voice that could only be heard by the two of us, she whispered into my ear, "I'm sorry, Nonomiya-kun..." I became giddy.<!-- Maybe there's a more fitting expression. Taken straight out from the dictionary. -EEE -->


"...That ''sneeze'' back then wasn't on purpose, honestly?"


—that Youko Tsukimori was not an ordinary girl.

I didn't turn around to her anymore, for my "temperature" wasn't going to decrease as long as I was near her.

Right now, I could not keep a cool head in her presence.",
